<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
Given that:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log a = {14}, \quad \log b = {15}, \quad \log c = {7}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Find:
<me>
\log\left(\frac{ab}{c}\right)
</me>
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We apply the logarithm rules step by step.
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Use the product rule:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log(ab) = \log a + \log b
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Use the quotient rule:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log\left(\frac{ab}{c}\right) = \log(ab) - \log c
</me>
</p>

<p>
Substitute:
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {14} + {15} - {7}
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
= {22}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>22</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>